<div id="pf3dd" class="pf w17 hea" data-page-no="3dd"><div class="pc pc3dd w17 hea"><div class="t mca3 x71 h4 y1f48 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6 </div><div class="t m5 x4a h4 y1f48 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m1897 x1a h2f y107f ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">T II E SABBATII </div><div class="t ma87 x71 h4 y1f60 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the seventh day of the weekly cycle for all time to conic,&quot; because </div><div class="t m3bb x71 h4 y1414 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that in it He </div><div class="t m359 xa h30 y1fba ff6 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">had rested.&quot; </div><div class="t m2dc x48 h4 yf1f ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">8. GOD created the earth for man. He set apart the seventh </div><div class="t m3de x71 h4 y1c75 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">day as a memorial of that work, and, as creation pertained to the </div><div class="t m695 x71 h4 y1dbf ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">earth, and the earth was created for the entire race, so the Sabbath </div><div class="t mb83 x71 h4 y1086 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">must have been made for the entire race. It would be incon-</div><div class="t mdc9 x71 h4 y15ce ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">gruous and illogical to consider it otherwise. </div><div class="t m27b x55 h63 y13f5 ff1 fs1e fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">LESSON 11.--July 13, 1895. </div><div class="t m2ce x60 h32 y2097 ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">THE DESIGN AND DAY OF THE SABBATH. </div><div class="t m35b x14 h2f y10e5 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">SCRIPTURE READING . —Jer. 10:10-12; Ps. 33 : 0; Ex. 20 ; 11; Isa. 40 : 28; Ex. </div><div class="t m1362 x71 h2f y13e3 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">31 :17; Ps. 111 ; 2-4; 135 :13; Eze. 20 :12, 20; 1 John 3 :7; 2 :29; Isa. 54 : 17. </div><div class="t m33b x5d h2f y1cdb ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">REviEw QUESTIONS. </div><div class="t mb49 xa4 h4 y1cdb ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">—(a) When was the Sabbath made? </div><div class="t m7b6 x62 h1b y418 ff6 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(b) </div><div class="t m415 x94 h4 y418 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">By </div><div clas